    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear u on the planning part, but it feels like the pushback against it usually just comes from people who want to keep neighborhoods exclusive or stop progress. like, is there actually any legitimate reason to be against density, or is it mostly just NIMBYism and protecting property values at the expense of everyone else?",
